Because we're saved and we are God's workmanship and we are to walk in good works.

660
00:54:45,380 --> 00:54:53,060
Not to be saved, not to stay saved, but because I am saved and because I have a new nature.

661
00:54:53,060 --> 00:54:57,300
You know how many times I wanted to go to church before I got saved?

662
00:54:57,300 --> 00:55:00,460
You know how many times I wanted to read the Bible before I got saved?

663
00:55:00,680 --> 00:55:08,600
But all of a sudden you get saved and it's, what can I do for my master?

664
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:11,840
Not so that I can earn more of his love because he loves me.

665
00:55:11,840 --> 00:55:13,640
He loves me.

666
00:55:13,640 --> 00:55:18,320
It's not so that I can earn his grace because he's gracious.

667
00:55:18,320 --> 00:55:22,480
It's not so that I could have more mercy because his mercy endureth forever.

668
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:27,600
It's because I have a new nature and it's because true faith works.

669
00:55:27,600 --> 00:55:28,600
Talk is cheap.

670
00:55:28,740 --> 00:55:32,940
And so James says, show me your faith.

671
00:55:32,940 --> 00:55:36,900
I'm going to show you my faith by my works.

672
00:55:36,900 --> 00:55:38,580
Try to show me your faith without works.

673
00:55:38,580 --> 00:55:41,760
It's going to be near impossible.

674
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:47,020
We could use so many illustrations this morning to try to illustrate the fact that things

675
00:55:47,020 --> 00:55:54,660
we exercise faith in and how our behavior is impacted by that.

676
00:55:54,660 --> 00:55:58,260
I shared with a man years ago, probably at this point, Holland and I weren't even married,

677
00:55:58,280 --> 00:56:03,440
we'll be married for 25 years this year, just in a few months, so it was probably 27, 28

678
00:56:03,440 --> 00:56:04,440
years ago.

679
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:09,660
And I was talking to a man and I was on the second level of a mall and the King of Prussia

680
00:56:09,660 --> 00:56:13,960
mall up in Pennsylvania, it's a very large mall up there and I was in that mall, I was

681
00:56:13,960 --> 00:56:17,560
on the second level, I was working through Bible college at a place that I don't think

682
00:56:17,560 --> 00:56:20,660
exists anymore, Payless Shoe Store.

683
00:56:20,660 --> 00:56:24,800
And I was on break and I was talking to a man on a bench and he said, I don't believe

684
00:56:24,800 --> 00:56:25,920
nothing.

685
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:26,920
Just like that.

686
00:56:27,080 --> 00:56:32,400
Kind of agnostic, whatever he wanted to call himself and I said, well, do you believe in

687
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:33,400
gravity?

688
00:56:33,400 --> 00:56:34,400
No.

689
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:36,400
I said, really?

690
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:40,160
I don't know why I asked that question, but I did, just the Holy Spirit kind of led me

691
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:43,120
to ask that question out of so many that I could ask.

692
00:56:43,120 --> 00:56:44,120
And he said, no.

693
00:56:44,120 --> 00:56:48,400
I said, okay, why don't you just kind of step over that little railing there and just kind

694
00:56:48,400 --> 00:56:49,400
of step off?

695
00:56:49,400 --> 00:56:50,400
And he's like, no.

696
00:56:50,400 --> 00:56:52,240
I said, why not?

697
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:55,960
He said, because I'll fall.

698
00:56:55,960 --> 00:56:56,960
Why?

699
00:56:56,960 --> 00:56:57,960
Gravity.

700
00:56:57,960 --> 00:56:58,960
Right?

701
00:56:58,960 --> 00:56:59,960
It's simple.

702
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:05,320
There's a law of gravity.

703
00:57:05,320 --> 00:57:10,520
So he was not going to step over the railing, though he said he did not believe in gravity.

704
00:57:10,520 --> 00:57:13,760
You know what his behavior revealed to me?

705
00:57:13,760 --> 00:57:17,320
That he believed in gravity, right?

706
00:57:17,320 --> 00:57:20,060
So what does your behavior reveal?

707
00:57:20,060 --> 00:57:22,440
What does my behavior reveal?

708
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:24,240
Do I really believe this book?

709
00:57:25,240 --> 00:57:27,240
Do I really believe that it's true?

710
00:57:27,240 --> 00:57:32,640
Do I really believe that people are going to die and spend eternity in the lake of fire?

711
00:57:32,640 --> 00:57:37,640
Do I really believe that God wants me to be a witness, to share a gospel tract, to share

712
00:57:37,640 --> 00:57:38,640
a word of testimony?

713
00:57:38,640 --> 00:57:44,640
Do I really believe what the book teaches?

714
00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:46,920
Or do I just say?

715
00:57:46,920 --> 00:57:48,960
Because talk is cheap.

716
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:51,160
Talk is cheap.

717
00:57:51,160 --> 00:57:56,840
And so show me, is what James says, your faith by your works.

718
00:57:56,840 --> 00:58:00,040
Because the only thing, listen, God sees the heart.

719
00:58:00,040 --> 00:58:01,660
And I'm thankful for that.

720
00:58:01,660 --> 00:58:06,040
But the only thing someone can see, humanly speaking, is the outward.

721
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:08,040
That's all we can see.

722
00:58:08,040 --> 00:58:10,960
And so you say that you believe?

723
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:15,720
I'm going to know what you believe by observing how you behave.

724
00:58:15,720 --> 00:58:16,880
What does the evidence say?

725
00:58:16,880 --> 00:58:18,800
What does the evidence say?

726
00:58:18,800 --> 00:58:22,040
Do we have true faith?

727
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:24,200
Because true faith works.

728
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:25,200
Let's pray.

729
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:26,200
Father, we love you.

730
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:27,320
We thank you so much for loving us.

731
00:58:27,320 --> 00:58:29,260
We thank you for the word of God.

732
00:58:29,260 --> 00:58:30,440
We thank you for the truth.

733
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:33,520
We thank you that we can compare scripture with scripture.

734
00:58:33,520 --> 00:58:43,760
We thank you that genuine conversion is only by faith.

735
00:58:44,760 --> 00:58:49,720
Lord, maybe there's someone here this morning that needs to be saved by the grace of God.

736
00:58:49,720 --> 00:58:51,300
Maybe they've rejected the message.

737
00:58:51,300 --> 00:58:53,080
Maybe they don't believe it to be true.

738
00:58:53,080 --> 00:58:56,640
They've rejected time and again.

739
00:58:56,640 --> 00:59:02,680
The Holy Spirit so sweetly used the word of God today to pierce their heart, to convince

740
00:59:02,680 --> 00:59:08,720
them of truth, to convict them of their own sin, of Christ's righteousness, of judgment

741
00:59:08,720 --> 00:59:13,120
to come, that it is true that whosoever is not found written in the book of life is cast

742
00:59:13,120 --> 00:59:17,040
in the lake of fire.

743
00:59:17,040 --> 00:59:18,600
Maybe they need to be saved this morning.

744
00:59:18,600 --> 00:59:25,800
God, I pray that you'd work and draw that individual to yourself.

745
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:30,960
We also said that genuine conversion produces fruit.

746
00:59:30,960 --> 00:59:33,580
We've been saved to serve you.

747
00:59:33,580 --> 00:59:35,080
We are your workmanship.

748
00:59:35,080 --> 00:59:39,900
And God, I pray that we'd evaluate our lives, those of us that are saved this morning, evaluate

749
00:59:39,900 --> 00:59:45,060
our lives to see if that true faith is working.

750
00:59:45,060 --> 00:59:46,340
What's the evidence?

751
00:59:46,340 --> 00:59:49,980
Do we really believe you?

752
00:59:49,980 --> 00:59:54,060
Do we really believe that what you say in your word is true?

753
00:59:54,060 --> 00:59:57,580
Has it impacted our behavior?

754
00:59:57,580 --> 01:00:01,580
Is it evidence through what we do day by day?

755
01:00:01,580 --> 01:00:03,900
Lord, would you work in this moment?

756
01:00:03,900 --> 01:00:11,900
I have a brief invitation. I pray that you would work in hearts and lives. Lord, we've heard, but now help us to respond.

757
01:00:11,900 --> 01:00:18,900
I pray, Father, that you would be glorified through every decision that's made. For it's in Christ's name we pray. Would you stand with me?

